div.div: Each section can have one or more metrics logged. Metrics for instance might be seeding rate, yield or application rate, but also depth, or width.
- Geometry (new metricValue for each new geometry point)
- Distance (new metricValue every <distanceTrigger metres or feet)
- OnChange (new metricValue when the value changes)
- ExternalTrigger (new metricValue when something happens on the device controller).

if Geometry trigger is chosen, and no triggerGeometry is supplied, the operation loggedGeometry should be used instead. In other circumstances, triggerGeometry should be populated with the points of new metricValues.
